From: Murat Kozan <muratkozan350@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Apr 2023 21:30:36 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] SystemUI: Reduce screenshot dismiss delay to 2 seconds

3 seconds is enough in most cases. Keeping the overlay around for too
long forces the user to dismiss it manually, which is a regression
compared to the Android 10's screenshot notification UI.
---
 .../com/android/systemui/screenshot/ScreenshotController.java   | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/screenshot/ScreenshotController.java b/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/screenshot/ScreenshotController.java
index 6cb7e1e37710d..000924d0e34b5 100644
--- a/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/screenshot/ScreenshotController.java
+++ b/packages/SystemUI/src/com/android/systemui/screenshot/ScreenshotController.java
@@ -244,7 +244,7 @@ interface TransitionDestination {
 
 
     private static final int MESSAGE_CORNER_TIMEOUT = 2;
-    private static final int SCREENSHOT_CORNER_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MILLIS = 6000;
+    private static final int SCREENSHOT_CORNER_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MILLIS = 2500;
 
     // From WizardManagerHelper.java
     private static final String SETTINGS_SECURE_USER_SETUP_COMPLETE = "user_setup_complete";
